MasterProX/Andrew: He's probably one of my best friends on Avicus by now. We met a few months ago in the TGC (Apollo) chat, and he's a very skilled player who knows how to work in a team. See you in the L.A. Philharmonic.
kycrafft: Ky is unlike anyone I've ever met. While being a skilled player in scrimmages and practice sessions, he is amazing in the clan chat, telling jokes and maintaining a positive atmosphere.
Heartless: Heat is another old friend on Avicus. I've rushed with him numerous times, and we've had some amazing times together in the Spamship chat, Berzerk chat, and other clan chats.
_Jasun: To be honest, I don't really know much about Jasun except that his skills are exceptional. Though quiet in the clan chat, he almost always attends practice sessions and is a loyal and valuable teammate.
DemApplez/Silent: I don't know much about Silent either, since he's mostly silent in the chat. However, just like Jasun, his extraordinary skills make up for his absence in the clan chat.
Steven5703: Like the two above, I don't know much about Steven, but he's a valuable player who's loyal to the team and provides to the clan chat a positive atmosphere.
FIyHacks/Seth: I've known Seth for almost two years, back when I was accepted to FanC. As one of the most skilled rushers I've known, he and I have played together in numerous clans, including FanC, Berzerk, and Immortality.
Hockey_: I don't think I've ever seen him talk in the clan chat, nor have I seen him in-game, so I basically know nothing about him.
JanetReyes/Amba: Amba is always chill, both in the clan chat and in-game. Though he used to be an asshole to me before he was banned, he is now one of the friendliest people I've ever met.
RefuseToSink: She's always chill, friendly, and fun to be around, both in-game and in the clan chat.

Snoozin/Badger: Though I knew Badger for a while, we haven't really talked much. He's a really chill and friendly player who shows complete loyalty to the team.
GetRacket_/Smitdalt: I've known Smit for a while, though we haven't really talked either. I don't know much about him except for his skills in-game.
Jiphy: I'll be honest here. I have absolutely no idea who this guy is, since he was only accepted two hours ago.
Alien: Yes, I know he isn't in the team anymore, but I think it's necessary to include him anyway. He was one of the most valuable players, and I'm glad I invited him to the team months ago. His skills deserve serious respect, and his dirty mind brings constant laughter to the clan chat.

Thank you, Berzerk, for helping each other through tough times, supporting each other, and being some of the most amazing people I have ever met.
